                    "comment": "lihalite commented on pull request #3878: ARROW-4421: handle large RPC messages in Flight\nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/3878#discussion_r264823916\n \n \n\n ##########\n File path: cpp/src/arrow/flight/client.cc\n ##########\n @@ -198,6 +198,8 @@ class FlightClient::FlightClientImpl {\n     grpc::ChannelArguments args;\n     // Try to reconnect quickly at first, in case the server is still starting up\n     args.SetInt(GRPC_ARG_INITIAL_RECONNECT_BACKOFF_MS, 100);\n+    // Receive messages of any size\n+    args.SetMaxReceiveMessageSize(-1);\n \n Review comment:\n   Note the issue in https://nanxiao.me/en/message-length-setting-in-grpc/ was fixed in https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/13553\n \n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on to GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
